        <!-- Page 3: Kikuyu -->
        <section class="page">
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="grass-page-card">
                    <img src="kikuyu.JPG" alt="kikuyu">
                    <div class="grass-info-large">
                        <h2>Kikuyu Grass</h2>
                        <p> Kikuyu grass stands out as a versatile and resilient choice for creating tough, 
                            beautiful gardens that can withstand everyday use while maintaining an attractive appearance.
                             Originally introduced for erosion control and forage purposes, this hardy, cost-effective grass establishes itself quickly,
                             making it an excellent option for homeowners and landscapers looking to develop lush lawns without extensive initial effort.
                             Its popularity extends to lawns, parks, and sports fields due to its ability to thrive in various conditions, 
                            though it does require regular mowing to keep its vigorous spread in check.</p>
                        <p><strong>Growth</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li> Kikuyu is a creeping, aggressive, and coarse perennial grass that spreads efficiently through runners, including both stolons 
                                (above-ground stems) and rhizomes (underground stems), allowing it to cover large areas rapidly.</li>
                            <li>This quick-spreading nature enables it to form a dense,
                                thick turf that provides excellent ground coverage, making it ideal for areas where a robust lawn is desired.</li>
                            <li>Additionally, Kikuyu recovers strongly from damage,
                                whether from heavy use, wear and tear, or environmental stresses, which makes it particularly well-suited for active yards, play areas, 
                               and high-traffic zones where other grasses might struggle to bounce back.
                               </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Appearance</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li> With its bold, coarse texture, Kikuyu offers a rugged yet appealing look that adds character to any garden or landscape.The grass features rich, vibrant green blades that maintain a lush appearance throughout the growing season, contributing to a visually striking lawn. </li>
                            <li>During summer flowering, it produces seed heads that remain hidden within the leaf structure, only revealing long, white, thread-like stamens, which adds a subtle, 
                                natural elegance without overwhelming the overall aesthetic. This combination of texture and color ensures that Kikuyu creates a beautiful, 
                                enduring green space that enhances the beauty of sunny gardens and outdoor areas.
                                 </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Tolerance</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li> Kikuyu thrives in intense heat and drought conditions, demonstrating remarkable resilience that allows it to stay healthy even in challenging climates with limited
                                water availability.</li>
                            <li>It handles heavy foot traffic with ease, making it a reliable choice for paths, sports fields, and family-friendly yards where durability is key.
                                While it prefers full sun, Kikuyu also tolerates moderate shade, providing flexibility for gardens with varying light exposure </li>
                            <li>Overall, its hardy nature supports low-maintenance requirements once established, though consistent mowing helps manage its spread and keeps it looking its best.This resilient grass creates a durable, great for play areas, paths, and sunny gardens, 
                                offering long-term value through its quick establishment, erosion control benefits, and ability to adapt to a range of environmental demands. </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="nav-arrow left"><i class="fas fa-chevron-left"></i></div>
            <div class="nav-arrow right"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></div>
        </section>

        <!-- Page 4: LM Berea -->
        <section class="page">
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="grass-page-card">
                    <img src="LM Berea" alt="LM Berea">
                    <div class="grass-info-large">
                        <h2>LM Berea</h2>
                        <p>LM Berea grass, scientifically known as *Dactyloctenium australe*, is a popular indigenous South African creeping perennial that excels in creating beautiful, low-maintenance lawns, particularly in shaded or semi-shaded areas. 
                            Recognized for its broad, dark green leaves and soft texture, this versatile grass is an excellent choice for lawns, parks, and erosion control projects. It grows moderately fast—faster than Buffalo but slower than Kikuyu—allowing it to establish reliably without overwhelming aggressiveness.
                             As a low-maintenance option, it requires less frequent mowing and adapts well to a wide variety of soil conditions, including sand, gravel, and loamy soils, where it helps stabilize the ground effectively.
                             </p>
                             <p><strong>Growth</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li> LM Berea spreads steadily as a creeping perennial, forming a reliable and even turf that provides good coverage over time.</li>
                            <li> While not as aggressive as Kikuyu, its moderate growth rate ensures quicker establishment than slower varieties like Buffalo, making it a balanced option for homeowners seeking a lawn that fills in efficiently without constant intervention. </li>
                            <li> It recovers adequately from wear and is particularly suited for areas needing soil stabilization, offering practical erosion control benefits.
                                </li>
                            <li>High-quality appearance perfect for elegant lawns</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Appearance</strong></p>

                        <ul>
                            <li>This grass features broad, dark green leaves with a notably soft texture, creating an inviting and lush appearance that feels pleasant underfoot. </li>
                            <li>The overall look is refined and uniform, contributing to an attractive, well-manicured lawn that enhances shaded garden spaces with its rich color and gentle feel.
                                </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Tolerance</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>LM Berea demonstrates excellent performance in shade and semi-shade, along with strong tolerance for drought and heat, making it highly adaptable to challenging South African climates. </li>
                            <li>It handles moderate foot traffic well and thrives across diverse soil types, while requiring minimal upkeep once established. </li>
                            <li>Though not as leafy as some forage grasses, it is palatable and can be utilized by animals if needed.
                                    This resilient, indigenous grass creates a durable, low-maintenance lawn that's ideal for shaded gardens, parks, and eco-conscious landscapes, providing long-term beauty and functionality with less effort than more demanding varieties.
                                     </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="nav-arrow left"><i class="fas fa-chevron-left"></i></div>
            <div class="nav-arrow right"><i class="fas fa-chevron-right"></i></div>
        </section>

        <!-- Page 5: Buffalo grass -->
        <section class="page">
            <div class="page-content">
                <div class="grass-page-card">
                    <img src="Buffalo.JPG" alt="Buffalo grass">
                    <div class="grass-info-large">
                        <h2>Buffalo grass</h2>
                        <p>Buffalo grass (*Bouteloua dactyloides*), particularly modern varieties like Legacy Buffalo, is a warm-season native turfgrass renowned for its exceptional drought resistance and low-maintenance requirements, making it a sustainable choice for eco-friendly, prairie-style lawns.
                                Known for its fine-textured blue-green blades that turn tan during winter dormancy, this hardy grass prefers full sun and spreads via stolons (above-ground stems). 
                               It grows slowly—which contributes to reduced mowing frequency and lower costs over time—but can be more expensive initially and slower to establish or repair compared to faster-spreading options.
                                Once mature, it thrives with minimal water and fertilizer, ideal for homeowners prioritizing sustainability. </p>
                                <p><strong>Growth</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>As a slow-growing perennial, Buffalo grass establishes gradually, requiring moist soil during the initial phase but significantly less water thereafter. </li>
                            <li> It spreads through stolons to form a solid turf, though its deliberate pace means patience is needed for full coverage.  </li>
                            <li> This slower growth reduces the need for frequent mowing, making it a true low-maintenance option for larger areas.
                                </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Appearance</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li> Buffalo features hardy, fine-textured blades in a distinctive blue-green hue that provide a natural, prairie-inspired aesthetic.</li>
                            <li>The grass maintains an attractive look during the active season, with modern varieties offering improved color retention and some shade tolerance, resulting in a neat, understated lawn that blends seamlessly with native landscapes.
                                </li>
                        </ul>
                        <p><strong>Tolerance</strong></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Highly drought-tolerant and requiring low inputs of water and fertilizer, Buffalo excels in intense heat and dry conditions, staying resilient with minimal care. </li>
                            <li>It prefers full sun but shows improved shade tolerance in newer cultivars; however, it does not handle high foot traffic well, making it unsuitable for heavy-use areas like sports fields.
                                    Its eco-friendly nature supports water conservation and reduced chemical use.
                                   This resilient grass creates a durable, low-maintenance lawn that's perfect for sunny, low-traffic gardens and environmentally conscious homeowners, delivering long-term savings and a natural beauty that endures challenging weather extremes. </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
